SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 1093
By Southerland
A RESOLUTION to honor and commend Alayna Baes upon being
named the 2026 Boys & Girls Club of Morristown
Youth of the Year.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly pause in their
deliberations to salute those young citizens who, through their remarkable efforts, have
distinguished themselves as emerging community and state leaders of whom we can all be
proud; and
WHEREAS, one such deserving person is Alayna Baes, who was recently named the
2026 Boys & Girls Club of Morristown Youth of the Year; and
WHEREAS, Miss Baes, a student at Morristown-Hamblen High School West, has been a
member of the Boys & Girls Club of Morristown for nine years; and
WHEREAS, the Boys & Girls Clubs exist to serve youth and to be a safe place of
encouragement, character building, security, and love for children; and
WHEREAS, since 1947, the Youth of the Year program has been the Boys & Girls Clubs
of America's premier recognition program, celebrating the extraordinary achievements of Club
members; and
WHEREAS, Youth of the Year participants embody the values of leadership, service,
academic excellence, and healthy lifestyles; and
WHEREAS, Youth of the Year participants like Alayna Baes exemplify the critical impact
of Boys & Girls Clubs on the lives of young people; and
WHEREAS, through the Youth of the Year program, Miss Baes and other Youth of the
Year participants are able to showcase their talents and achievements, share their hopes and
dreams, and work toward a bright and positive future; and
SJR1093
017270
- 1 -

WHEREAS, Alayna Baes is a shining example that "GREAT FUTURES START HERE"
at Boys & Girls Clubs; and
WHEREAS, the success of this State, the strength of our communities, and the overall
vitality of American society depend, in great measure, upon the dedication of young people like
Alayna Baes, who use their considerable talents and resources to serve others and who should
be specially recognized for their public and community service; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we honor and commend Alayna Baes upon being
named the 2026 Boys & Girls Club of Morristown Youth of the Year and extend to her our best
wishes for every future success.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
